# Copy this file to ".env" and fill in your Firebase web config.
# These values come from the Firebase console (Project settings > Your apps).
# NOTE: a Firebase web apiKey is not a secret (it ships in the client bundle),
# but keeping it in .env makes it easy to swap projects per environment.
#
# The values below are the ones found embedded in the v6.9 dist (project genro-b74de).
# They are provided as defaults so `npm run dev` works out of the box; replace
# them if you point this project at a different Firebase project.

